EXTRACTED VALUE: Lacking the intensity and lavish budget of a "Need for Speed." [Issue#25, p.101]
It’s hard to completely dismiss the game as trash, but it’s harder not to feel like the game should be giving you a lot more.
Bare-bones, unpolished and uninspired. When you don't even have any sort of ending wrap-up screen for the Season mode, you know you're in trouble.
A brain numbingly dull title that is only partially saved by its above average presentation.
A misguided effort to streamline the experience and create gameplay where realism comes before responsiveness.
